  "texts": [
    "This is very likely due to less trainable parameters when we perform DPO on them with QLoRA adapters (which only finetunes <2% of all trainable parameters), as compared to full-model finetuning for smaller models like mGPT and BLOOM-1.7B (see Appendix D for QLoRA training for BLOOM-1.7B).",
    "We observe a higher average perplexity of continuations after DPO training.",
    "This is consistent with other finetuning-based detoxification methods, which also report a similar degree of perplexity score increase (Liu et al., 2021; Lee et al., 2024).",
    "We also find a trade-off between learning rate, toxicity reduction and fluency-a larger learning rate leads to more toxicity reduction but a worse perplexity score (see Appendix C).",
    "Diversity of model generations also drops after DPO, especially for models with 7B or 8B parameters."
  ],
